[3
Date: October 15, 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: CNN, 15 Oct 2001 [edited
<http://www.cnn.com/2001/HEALTH/conditions/10/15/anthrax/index.html>

More anthrax spores found in Florida
------------------------------------
A small number of anthrax spores were discovered in a Boca Raton,
Florida, U.S. Postal Service mail-sorting facility that handled mail for the
tabloid publishing company where the first anthrax exposures were
discovered, Florida health officials said Monday. The bacteria were found in
a remote section of the building, which remained open Monday even after the
discovery was announced. The facility is not open to the public. All
employees are undergoing prophylactic treatment with antibiotics and are
undergoing testing to determine whether they have been exposed to the
bacteria, a spokesman for the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention
told CNN.
The building was one of 3 tested after it was confirmed that a photo editor
at the tabloid The Sun had contracted the inhaled form of the bacteria. He
later died, the first such death in the United States since 1976.
