[5
Date: 15 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AP Online [edited
<http://www.nandotimes.com/nation/story/141383p-1404725c.html>

Child of ABC Employee Gets Anthrax
----------------------------------
A child of an ABC News employee has been tested positive for anthrax, a
government official said Monday. The official, speaking on condition of
anonymity, said the child is being treated with antibiotics and is expected
to recover. The anthrax diagnosed in the child is the type that is absorbed
through cuts or scratches in the skin, not the more dangerous inhaled
variety, the source said.
The child had visited the ABC newsroom in New York in the last week,
probably 8 Oct 2001, the source said. [During a CNN interview this evening,
NYC Mayor Giuliani said that the child had visited the newsroom on 28 Sep
2001. - Mod.ES
[If this child was infected with cutaneous anthrax at ABC, this is a new
target site -- though not unexpected. The visiting date is of concern. -
Mod.MHJ
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[There have been some comments for a number of days about the severity of
the second Florida patient's condition being downplayed by the Florida
authorities. The above would confirm such concerns. The franking date on
Senator Daschle's letter, 18 Sep 2001 -- the same date and post office as
the letter to NBC, New York, would indicate that this latest revelation is
not of a third posting but of a second letter in an apparent second patch
of letters mailed. If there are other contaminated letters, presumably they
will be revealed in due course. Some miscellaneous news culled from earlier
reports: The Nevada people tested negative, 4/6 on confirmation, 2/6 on
preliminary only. The 5 seropositive people in Florida had "slightly
elevated" titres. - Mod.MHJ
